## Code Style Rules

### Package Imports
- **Always use package imports instead of fully qualified class names**
- Never write full package paths (e.g., `com.github.istin.dmtools.ai.ollama.OllamaAIClient`) unless there's a naming conflict
- Use import statements at the top of the file (e.g., `import com.github.istin.dmtools.ai.ollama.OllamaAIClient;`)
- Only use fully qualified names when there are multiple classes with the same name from different packages that would conflict
- Examples:
  - ✅ Good: `import com.github.istin.dmtools.ai.ollama.OllamaAIClient;` then use `OllamaAIClient`
  - ❌ Bad: `new com.github.istin.dmtools.ai.ollama.OllamaAIClient(...)`
  - ✅ Good (when conflict exists): `new java.util.Date()` vs `new java.sql.Date()`

### General Guidelines
- Always respond in English. No comments in code in Russian.
- Don't write documentation unless it's not asked
- Prefer clean, readable code with proper imports over verbose fully qualified names
